
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ms-emu-eaptlscert-03.txt'>
    <title>"Handling Large Certificates and Long Certificate Chains in TLS-based EAP Methods", Mohit Sethi, John Mattsson, Sean Turner</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ms-emu-eaptlscert-03.txt</link>
    <description>EAP-TLS and other TLS-based EAP methods are widely deployed and used for network access authentication.  Large certificates and long certificate chains combined with authenticators that drop an EAP session after only 40 - 50 round-trips is a major deployment problem. This memo looks at the this problem in detail and describes the potential solutions available.</description>
    <dc:date>2019-05-26T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
